bibl.note: Our transcription is based on a digital image of the microfilmed original.

div1.p: In the District Court the 3rd Judicial District of Washington Territory holding terms at Seattle, King County
In the matter of the application of William Jewett for writ of Habeas Corpus

Upon reading and filing the petition of William Jewett duly signed and verified by him, whereby it appears that he is illegally imprisoned and restrained of his liberty by John H. McGraw Sheriff of said King County at the county Jail of said County for the reason that there is no information or complaint as required by law, on file against him the said Jewett charging him with any crime from which it appears to me that a writ of Habeas Corpus ought to issue, it is ordered that a writ of Habeas Corpus issue out of and under the Deal of the said Court of said District directed to the said John H. McGraw Sheriff as aforesaid commanding him to have the body of said

William Jewett before me in the court room of said court at the City of Seattle in said county and Territory of one the 6th April 1889 at forthwith o'clock of that day, to do, and receive what shall then and there be considered concerning the said petitioner, William Jewett together with the said time and cause of his detention, and that you have then and there this writ.
Filed April 5/89 W E Ledgerwood Clerk
